# Copy to .env.local (gitignored) and fill in.

# Credential for the "Google Photorealistic 3D" toggle in the 3D Model export.
# Accepts EITHER of two credential types — the app auto-detects which
# (services/tilesAuth.js):
#
#   1. Google Maps Platform API key ("AIza…") with the Map Tiles API enabled.
#      Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/tile.googleapis.com
#      NOTE: EEA/EU-billed projects are blocked from Photorealistic 3D Tiles
#      (HTTP 403) since 8 July 2025 — use option 2 instead.
#
#   2. Cesium ion access token (a JWT, "eyJ…"). Serves the same Google tiles
#      under Cesium's non-EEA credentials, bypassing the EEA block.
#      Token: https://ion.cesium.com/tokens (free account)
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
